    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><note>Il <rs key="#Princeps">principe</rs>
                            <persName key="#Princeps" ref="#people/303">Arechi II</persName> offre
                            al monastero di S. Sofia di <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/110"
                                >Benevento</placeName> (prosegue l'elenco iniziato con il doc.
                            3535):</note></ab>
                    <ab>(…) [6] Seu et <orgName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Wine #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3404"><rs key="#Churches">eclesia</rs> &lt;sic>
                            Sancti Iohannis</orgName> que fundata est in <geogName
                            key="#Gai #Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential" ref="#estates/3402"
                                ><rs key="#Gai #Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential">gaio</rs>
                            nostro <placeName ref="#places/3402"
                                key="#Uncertain_tradition #Gai #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fiscal_property #Churches"
                                >Casa Polluci</placeName></geogName> et ab ipsa ęcclesia largiti
                        sumus in <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/85"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Wine #Churches #Monasteries"><rs
                                key="#Landed_possessions #Wine #Churches #Monasteries"
                                >monasterio</rs> Sancte Sophie</orgName>
                        <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >territorio</rs> hoc est ab ipsa ęcclesia <rs key="#Confinia">usque</rs>
                        in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3403"
                                >Fertore</placeName></rs> ubi <rs key="#Rivers"><placeName
                                ref="#places/3405" key="#Rivers">Acinia</placeName> flumen</rs> se
                        iun­git et <rs key="#Confinia">de alio latere</rs> quantum clausum habere
                        videtur et <rs key="#Wine">vineas</rs> que ibidem posite sunt. (…)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
